channel.title: Webclient - Cache Help
channel.description:
Okay, so i got my client working, and then converted to webclient fine, and when i move the cache that on my computer already into c:/ drive it works fine, but when i take it away, try to download cache, it downloads perfectly, but when it gets to unpacking, it seems to not unpack the files??? www.fusion-pkzz.webs.com, you'll see it'll download cache but the when unpacks it stuffs up, please help?
THIS BATCH IS FOR DEBUGGING THE EXECUTABLE JAR ONLY DOUBLE-CLICK THE "client.jar" TO RUN IT - Generated by: JAR Maker (http://www.goldenstudios.or.id/) C:\Documents and Settings\Ryan\Desktop\AAAAA>java -jar client.jar Cache.zip 65887717 java.io.FileNotFoundException: C:\Fusionpk_file_store_32\Data\Animation\custom.d at (The system cannot find the path specified) at java.io.FileOutputStream.open(Native Method) at java.io.FileOutputStream.(Unknown Source) at java.io.FileOutputStream.(Unknown Source) at CacheDownloader.unzip(CacheDownloader.java:219) at CacheDownloader.unZip(CacheDownloader.java:176) at CacheDownloader.downloadCache(CacheDownloader.java:78) at client.startUp(client.java:7811) at RSApplet.run(RSApplet.java:33) at client.run(client.java:5281) at java.lang.Thread.run(Unknown Source) java.io.FileNotFoundException: C:\Fusionpk_file_store_32\Maps\mapConfig.txt (The system cannot find the path specified) at java.io.FileInputStream.open(Native Method) at java.io.FileInputStream.(Unknown Source) at java.io.FileInputStream.(Unknown Source) at java.io.FileReader.(Unknown Source) at client.setNewMaps(client.java:64) at client.startUp(client.java:7812) at RSApplet.run(RSApplet.java:33) at client.run(client.java:5281) at java.lang.Thread.run(Unknown Source) java.lang.NegativeArraySizeException at client.drawLogo(client.java:3279) at client.startUp(client.java:7838) at RSApplet.run(RSApplet.java:33) at client.run(client.java:5281) at java.lang.Thread.run(Unknown Source) Error: loaderror Unpacking.. 35
thats the error i get, it says java.io.FileNotFoundException: C:\Fusionpk_file_store_32\Data\Animation\custom.d, but 1, that file is in the downloadable cache, and 2 it shouldnt be looking for it??? should it just unpack all those files inside the cache?
